      <body>Steve, I am not sure I understand what you say.

I could make work &quot;:distinct =&gt; true&quot; in a count like this (both in Rails 3beta2 and 2.3.5):

  Project.count(:name, :distinct =&gt; true)

For scope, is it something like this you want?:
  
  scope :uniq_names, :select =&gt; :name, :distinct =&gt; true

(You're right specifying :distinct in a scope does not work.)</body>
      <body-html>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Steve, I am not sure I understand what you say.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I could make work &quot;:distinct =&amp;gt; true&quot; in a count like this
(both in Rails 3beta2 and 2.3.5):&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Project.count(:name, :distinct =&amp;gt; true)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For scope, is it something like this you want?:&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;scope :uniq_names, :select =&amp;gt; :name, :distinct =&amp;gt; true&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;(You're right specifying :distinct in a scope does not
work.)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</body-html>
